  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 66-year-old man is brought to the emergency department by his sister because of a 10-day history of fever, chills, and myalgias. Five days ago, he went to the physician with the same symptoms, for which he was prescribed acetaminophen, but his symptoms have not improved. During the past 4 days, he has developed a nonproductive cough and mild shortness of breath. He works as a shepherd and has been working more hours per day than usual because it is lambing season. He lives with his sister, who does not have any symptoms. His immunizations are up to date. His temperature is 39.2ºC (102.6ºF), pulse is 68/min, respirations are 17/min, and blood pressure is 132/70 mm Hg. Pulse oximetry on room air shows an oxygen saturation of 93%. Physical examination shows scattered inspiratory crackles and wheezes in both lungs. There is a new-onset holosystolic murmur best heard at the apex that radiates to the left axilla. The liver is palpated 4 cm below the right costal margin. Laboratory studies show:\n\n\nHemoglobin\n13.5 g/dL\n\n\nLeukocyte count\n13,000/mm3\n\n\n\nPlatelet count\n110,000/mm3\n\n\nErythrocyte sedimentation rate\n39 mm/h\n\n\nSerum\n\n\n\nAST\n320 U/L\n\n\nALT\n298 U/L\n\n\nTotal bilirubin\n0.9 mg/dL\n\n\nBlood cultures are negative. An x-ray of the chest shows interstitial infiltrates and lobar opacities in both lungs. Which of the following is the most likely causal pathogen?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Brucella melitensis"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Plasmodium ovale"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Rickettsia rickettsii"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Coxiella burnetii"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Influenza A virus"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lf0vm2&anker=Z22fda4defe397ffa898278e4a1d9b796\" data-learningcard-id=\"lf0vm2\" data-anker=\"Z22fda4defe397ffa898278e4a1d9b796\" data-section-id=\"eS0xA2\">Brucella melitensis</a></i> is the causal <span data-sememe-id=\"XgW9Fk0\">pathogen</span> of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lf0vm2&anker=Zdac34c45f360e2914d6019e042e4816b\" data-learningcard-id=\"lf0vm2\" data-anker=\"Zdac34c45f360e2914d6019e042e4816b\" data-sememe-id=\"Ej08XT\">brucellosis</a>. This condition manifests with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a>, <span data-sememe-id=\"xZcEda0\">myalgias</span>, chills, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a>, <span data-sememe-id=\"VpcGoW0\">hepatitis</span>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=CS0qbf&anker=Zd1c6edf460701976c172357533193fca\" data-learningcard-id=\"CS0qbf\" data-anker=\"Zd1c6edf460701976c172357533193fca\" data-section-id=\"UYaboQ\" data-sememe-id=\"4KX3g_\">endocarditis</a>. It is also more common in shepherds because <i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sn0ysg&anker=Z9e4cf35eb782e20f8edea18b88fa0161\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sn0ysg\" data-anker=\"Z9e4cf35eb782e20f8edea18b88fa0161\" data-section-id=\"s0ctha0\" data-sememe-id=\"PjYW06\">Brucella</a></i> is transmitted through the ingestion of <span data-sememe-id=\"xVeE9B0\">raw</span> milk produced by infected animals or the inhalation of aerosols from the secretions of infected livestock. However, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-sememe-id=\"rk0f6T\">pneumonia</a> is a rare feature in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lf0vm2&anker=Zdac34c45f360e2914d6019e042e4816b\" data-learningcard-id=\"lf0vm2\" data-anker=\"Zdac34c45f360e2914d6019e042e4816b\" data-sememe-id=\"Ej08XT\">brucellosis</a>. Moreover, patients with this condition usually have <span data-sememe-id=\"85XONA\">arthralgia</span>. Finally, <i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sn0ysg&anker=Z9e4cf35eb782e20f8edea18b88fa0161\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sn0ysg\" data-anker=\"Z9e4cf35eb782e20f8edea18b88fa0161\" data-section-id=\"s0ctha0\" data-sememe-id=\"PjYW06\">Brucella</a></i> can usually grow on <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">blood culture</a>, which is used to confirm the diagnosis.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Kf0UM2&anker=Z8ba9eb1b4eb0dcfbbedb1e5bdb9c2d89\" data-learningcard-id=\"Kf0UM2\" data-anker=\"Z8ba9eb1b4eb0dcfbbedb1e5bdb9c2d89\" data-section-id=\"_h05gf\" data-sememe-id=\"ckYa56\">Plasmodium ovale</a></i> is a causal <span data-sememe-id=\"XgW9Fk0\">pathogen</span> of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Kf0UM2&anker=Z1c9e15bc48db729a509c1c4d9382d180\" data-learningcard-id=\"Kf0UM2\" data-anker=\"Z1c9e15bc48db729a509c1c4d9382d180\" data-sememe-id=\"xj0EcT\">malaria</a>, which can manifest with high <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a>, chills, <span data-sememe-id=\"xZcEda0\">myalgias</span>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=XL09wg&anker=Z709336d8b15286caf8a83fc77a8f0f99\" data-learningcard-id=\"XL09wg\" data-anker=\"Z709336d8b15286caf8a83fc77a8f0f99\" data-section-id=\"eccxYY0\" data-sememe-id=\"RjXlZy\">hepatomegaly</a>. However, patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Kf0UM2&anker=Z1c9e15bc48db729a509c1c4d9382d180\" data-learningcard-id=\"Kf0UM2\" data-anker=\"Z1c9e15bc48db729a509c1c4d9382d180\" data-sememe-id=\"xj0EcT\">malaria</a> typically have intermittent spiking <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> as opposed to the prolonged <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> seen in this patient. In addition, features of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-sememe-id=\"rk0f6T\">pneumonia</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=CS0qbf&anker=Ze27bdb9905de29a08428042b9c679dcd\" data-learningcard-id=\"CS0qbf\" data-anker=\"Ze27bdb9905de29a08428042b9c679dcd\" data-section-id=\"U71bOR0\">acute endocarditis</a> are not consistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Kf0UM2&anker=Z1c9e15bc48db729a509c1c4d9382d180\" data-learningcard-id=\"Kf0UM2\" data-anker=\"Z1c9e15bc48db729a509c1c4d9382d180\" data-sememe-id=\"xj0EcT\">malaria</a>. Moreover, a history of travel to an <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Js0sDh&anker=Z2303208fe6d5dfa38ab9eafb83c6f0f7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Js0sDh\" data-anker=\"Z2303208fe6d5dfa38ab9eafb83c6f0f7\" data-section-id=\"wfWhok0\" data-sememe-id=\"dT0op2\">endemic</a> region, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rT0fH2&anker=Z958cf76990e9ccf502442ead34e224b0\" data-learningcard-id=\"rT0fH2\" data-anker=\"Z958cf76990e9ccf502442ead34e224b0\" data-sememe-id=\"pP0LfT\">hemolytic anemia</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jS0_z2&anker=Z5f49d92f52d702a9bee9b2538ad7b454\" data-learningcard-id=\"jS0_z2\" data-anker=\"Z5f49d92f52d702a9bee9b2538ad7b454\" data-section-id=\"Gx0BBR\" data-sememe-id=\"bu0Hp3\">jaundice</a> would also be expected.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sn0ysg&anker=Zbe570ae2d5b54adb02c83cd62ba8be95\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sn0ysg\" data-anker=\"Zbe570ae2d5b54adb02c83cd62ba8be95\" data-section-id=\"J0csSa0\" data-sememe-id=\"AabRMH\">Rickettsia rickettsii</a></i> is the causal <span data-sememe-id=\"XgW9Fk0\">pathogen</span> of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=P70WNh&anker=Z3c478bea299df00acb311ad3ab32854d\" data-learningcard-id=\"P70WNh\" data-anker=\"Z3c478bea299df00acb311ad3ab32854d\" data-section-id=\"ft1k1i0\" data-sememe-id=\"J4Ys46\">Rocky Mountain spotted fever</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=P70WNh&anker=Z3c478bea299df00acb311ad3ab32854d\" data-learningcard-id=\"P70WNh\" data-anker=\"Z3c478bea299df00acb311ad3ab32854d\" data-section-id=\"ft1k1i0\" data-sememe-id=\"J4Ys46\">RMSF</a>), which can manifest with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a>, <span data-sememe-id=\"xZcEda0\">myalgias</span>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=XL09wg&anker=Z709336d8b15286caf8a83fc77a8f0f99\" data-learningcard-id=\"XL09wg\" data-anker=\"Z709336d8b15286caf8a83fc77a8f0f99\" data-section-id=\"eccxYY0\" data-sememe-id=\"RjXlZy\">hepatomegaly</a>. However, this condition does not cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-sememe-id=\"rk0f6T\">pneumonia</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=CS0qbf&anker=Ze27bdb9905de29a08428042b9c679dcd\" data-learningcard-id=\"CS0qbf\" data-anker=\"Ze27bdb9905de29a08428042b9c679dcd\" data-section-id=\"U71bOR0\">acute endocarditis</a>. In addition, a blanching <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Su0yq3&anker=Zd6507557ab4a474e9b1f51c444cd06b8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Su0yq3\" data-anker=\"Zd6507557ab4a474e9b1f51c444cd06b8\" data-section-id=\"7Ud4e60\">macular rash</a> and a history of a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4f03m2&anker=Z18c2c3f723227017146368887927f463\" data-learningcard-id=\"4f03m2\" data-anker=\"Z18c2c3f723227017146368887927f463\" data-section-id=\"mg0VD2\">tick bite</a> would be expected in a patient with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=P70WNh&anker=Z3c478bea299df00acb311ad3ab32854d\" data-learningcard-id=\"P70WNh\" data-anker=\"Z3c478bea299df00acb311ad3ab32854d\" data-section-id=\"ft1k1i0\" data-sememe-id=\"J4Ys46\">RMSF</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b><i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sn0ysg&anker=Zb4c4ba24616f5c11367ecd9577676fc4\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sn0ysg\" data-anker=\"Zb4c4ba24616f5c11367ecd9577676fc4\" data-section-id=\"J0csSa0\" data-sememe-id=\"-dYDsL\">Coxiella burnetii</a></i> </b></span>is the causal <span data-sememe-id=\"XgW9Fk0\">pathogen</span> of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lH0vqh&anker=Z969cf3526c691462664a8365f4e5bc33\" data-learningcard-id=\"lH0vqh\" data-anker=\"Z969cf3526c691462664a8365f4e5bc33\" data-sememe-id=\"_dY5sL\">Q fever</a>. This <span data-sememe-id=\"XgW9Fk0\">pathogen</span> is transmitted through the ingestion of <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><span data-sememe-id=\"xVeE9B0\">raw</span> milk</b></span> produced by infected animals or the inhalation of aerosols from the <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>secretions</b></span> of <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>infected livestock</b></span>. Accordingly, this rare condition is more common in shepherds, veterinarians, slaughterhouse workers, and farmers. Although ∼ 50% of patients with acute <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lH0vqh&anker=Z969cf3526c691462664a8365f4e5bc33\" data-learningcard-id=\"lH0vqh\" data-anker=\"Z969cf3526c691462664a8365f4e5bc33\" data-sememe-id=\"_dY5sL\">Q fever</a> are asymptomatic, some develop <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Bm0z3g&anker=Z5d4ae74d1fc68675546692a782da7e22\" data-learningcard-id=\"Bm0z3g\" data-anker=\"Z5d4ae74d1fc68675546692a782da7e22\" data-section-id=\"yDbdSD\" data-sememe-id=\"qS0C0f\">flulike symptoms</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z07556022d44dd36bf61f1021b006b0ae\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z07556022d44dd36bf61f1021b006b0ae\" data-section-id=\"MUaMdP\" data-sememe-id=\"YC0nqR\">atypical pneumonia</a>, <span data-sememe-id=\"VpcGoW0\">hepatitis</span>, and, in rare cases, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=CS0qbf&anker=Ze27bdb9905de29a08428042b9c679dcd\" data-learningcard-id=\"CS0qbf\" data-anker=\"Ze27bdb9905de29a08428042b9c679dcd\" data-section-id=\"U71bOR0\">acute endocarditis</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">Blood cultures</a> are usually negative, and the diagnosis is made via <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dP0odT&anker=Z9caa17c93bb6dbe2123337fd9f0032be\" data-learningcard-id=\"dP0odT\" data-anker=\"Z9caa17c93bb6dbe2123337fd9f0032be\" data-section-id=\"ztXrT-\" data-sememe-id=\"ag1QFT0\">immunofluorescence</a> assay. The first-line treatment is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z7be844e641e39c38bc679cc02f7f8285\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z7be844e641e39c38bc679cc02f7f8285\" data-section-id=\"fjck-X0\" data-sememe-id=\"6Oajtk\">doxycycline</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Z9f0876a200701e5fdece2e58aa965574\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Z9f0876a200701e5fdece2e58aa965574\" data-section-id=\"2acTPa0\" data-sememe-id=\"SYcyoa0\">Influenza A virus</a> is a causal <span data-sememe-id=\"XgW9Fk0\">pathogen</span> of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Bm0z3g&anker=Z7f6a08ed676ff91e0fd1a38ea649ecbd\" data-learningcard-id=\"Bm0z3g\" data-anker=\"Z7f6a08ed676ff91e0fd1a38ea649ecbd\" data-sememe-id=\"JL0sAg\">influenza</a>, which can manifest with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a>, chills, <span data-sememe-id=\"xZcEda0\">myalgias</span>, nonproductive <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a>, mild <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xq09CS&anker=Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xq09CS\" data-anker=\"Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-sememe-id=\"KaYUln\">dyspnea</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-sememe-id=\"rk0f6T\">pneumonia</a> in more severe cases. However, this condition does not cause new-onset <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Yh0ncf&anker=Z09a6f4ead95fb05ee29ab9e7d1219e33\" data-learningcard-id=\"Yh0ncf\" data-anker=\"Z09a6f4ead95fb05ee29ab9e7d1219e33\" data-sememe-id=\"A_YRI7\">mitral regurgitation</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rM0fJg&anker=Z574f0b0a2737041cfe4ba1db88e9ee5e\" data-learningcard-id=\"rM0fJg\" data-anker=\"Z574f0b0a2737041cfe4ba1db88e9ee5e\" data-section-id=\"ESc8YX0\" data-sememe-id=\"FQ0gBf\">holosystolic murmur</a> best heard at the apex that radiates to the left <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cK0a2S&anker=Za39fde93a66b2b4dcd919344fbbbe0a4\" data-learningcard-id=\"cK0a2S\" data-anker=\"Za39fde93a66b2b4dcd919344fbbbe0a4\" data-section-id=\"BJczwW0\" data-sememe-id=\"kP1mUS0\">axilla</a>) or <span data-sememe-id=\"VpcGoW0\">hepatitis</span>. Moreover, this patient's immunizations are up to date.</div>",
      "hint": "This patient's profession, history of prolonged fever, findings consistent with pneumonia (cough, dyspnea, hypoxemia, and x-ray findings), thrombocytopenia, acute endocarditis (new-onset mitral regurgitation), and hepatitis (hepatomegaly with elevated liver enzymes) suggest acute Q fever.",
